'''Chundawats''' are a [[Rajput]] clan and were powerful chiefs in the [[Mewar]] region during the 1700s.<ref>{{cite book |chapter=Drudges, Dancing Girls, Concubines: Female Slaves in Rajput Polity, 1500-1850 |page=148 |first=Ramya |last=Sreenivasan|authorlink=Ramya Sreenivasan |title=Slavery and South Asian History |editor1-first=Indrani |editor1-last=Chatterjee |editor2-first=Richard M. |editor2-last=Eaton |publisher=Indiana University Press |year=2006 |isbn=978-0-25311-671-0 |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Nsh8NHDQHlcC&pg=PA148}}</ref>

